---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site, withBase } from "@/data/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="Download - Kagura Player" description="Release status, requirements, installation, and safety information for Kagura Player 0.6.0 Preview on Windows." canonicalPath="/en/download/" lang="en">
  <header class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Windows / 0.6.0 Preview</p><h1>The release candidate<br />is in final verification.</h1><p class="lead">The app, installer, Pro licensing, and cloud AI connection have passed integration checks. Signed updates and public distribution materials remain launch gates.</p><div class="hero-actions">{site.downloadUrl ? <a class="button primary" href={site.downloadUrl}>Download for Windows</a> : <span class="button secondary" aria-disabled="true">Private beta in preparation</span>}<a class="button secondary" href={withBase("/en/changelog/")}>Read the changelog</a></div></div></header>
  <section class="content-band" id="release-status"><div class="container release-facts"><div><small>Current version</small><strong>{site.version}</strong></div><div><small>Planned support</small><strong>Windows 10 / 11 x64</strong></div><div><small>Verification</small><strong>App and licensing test suites pass</strong></div></div></section>
  <section class="content-band alt"><div class="container content-grid"><h2>What remains before release</h2><div class="prose"><p>The internal installer has passed installation, launch, bundled FFmpeg, Pro licensing, and cloud AI connection checks. Public distribution still requires matching source materials, license text, source location, and final review.</p><p>Signed update manifests, the public installer, production Stripe, and verified seller information must be completed before the private beta opens.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="content-band"><div class="container content-grid"><h2>Installation after launch</h2><div class="prose"><ol><li>Download the verified installer from this page.</li><li>Choose optional Explorer integration and file associations.</li><li>Run later installers as in-place updates. Favorites, subtitles, and settings stay in the user data directory.</li></ol><p><a href={withBase("/en/system-requirements/")}>Review system requirements</a></p></div></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
